<div class="review" data-review="11820" data-user="10616">
<a name="11820"></a>
<h3 class="review_header">



<a href="/dist/App-ChangeShebang">


App-ChangeShebang</a>

   (<a href="https://metacpan.org/release/App-ChangeShebang/">0.02</a>)



</h3>



<blockquote class="review_text">
Given that the name of this module/app is &quot;change shebang&quot; (instead of &quot;change shebang to samedir perl&quot;) perhaps this app can be made more generic? For example, I've had to change all shebangs from &quot;#!/usr/bin/env perl&quot; to &quot;#!perl&quot; and vice versa. Perhaps this module/app can become a tool to easily switch between shebangs.<br>

</blockquote>


<div class="review_footer">
<p class="review_attribution">
<a href="/user/stevenharyanto">Steven Haryanto</a> - 2014-07-05T23:43:48
