<div class="review" data-review="10224" data-user="10616">
<a name="10224"></a>
<h3 class="review_header">



<a href="/dist/Devel-FindPerl">


Devel-FindPerl</a>

   (<a href="https://metacpan.org/release/Devel-FindPerl/">0.004</a>)



</h3>



<blockquote class="review_text">
IMO the module should explain in the POD, in what cases using $^X is not enough or how it is different from Probe::Perl.<br><br>Anyway, quoting CPAN Testers' CPAN Authors FAQ, $^X is not enough when:<br>
1) perl was executed with a relative path and the script has chdir()ed; 2) because $^X originates in C's argv[0] (in the main() function) it is possible for the calling program to exec() in such a way that argv[0] isn't the path to the interpreter; 3) HP/UX can do weird stuff in scripts that use #!; 4) VMS. (Not clear about #4 though :) ).
</blockquote>


<div class="review_footer">
<p class="review_attribution">
<a href="/user/stevenharyanto">Steven Haryanto</a> - 2012-07-25T18:08:57
(<a href="/dist/Devel-FindPerl#10224">permalink</a>)
